017package org.apache.juneau.bean.html5;

022/**
023 * DTO for an HTML <a class="doclink" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/html5/sections.html#the-h1,-h2,-h3,-h4,-h5,-and-h6-elements">&lt;h3&gt;</a>
024 * element.
025 *
026 * <p>
027 * The h3 element represents a third-level heading in a document or section. It is used to
028 * mark up subsections that are hierarchically below h2 elements. The h3 element is typically
029 * used to organize content into smaller subsections and is important for creating a logical
030 * document structure. It is typically rendered in a smaller font size than h2 but larger
031 * than h4 elements.
032 *
033 * <h5 class='section'>Examples:</h5>
034 * <p class='bcode w800'>
035 *    <jk>import static</jk> org.apache.juneau.bean.html5.HtmlBuilder.*;
036 * 
037 *    <jc>// Simple subsection heading</jc>
038 *    H3 <jv>simple</jv> = <jsm>h3</jsm>(<js>"Basic Configuration"</js>);
039 * 
040 *    <jc>// H3 with styling</jc>
041 *    H3 <jv>styled</jv> = <jsm>h3</jsm>(<js>"Advanced Settings"</js>)
042 *       ._class(<js>"subsection-title"</js>);
043 * 
044 *    <jc>// H3 with complex content</jc>
045 *    H3 <jv>complex</jv> = <jsm>h3</jsm>(
046 *       <js>"Step 3: "</js>,
047 *       <jsm>strong</jsm>(<js>"Database Setup"</js>),
048 *       <js>" "</js>,
049 *       <jsm>em</jsm>(<js>"(Optional)"</js>)
050 *    );
051 * 
052 *    <jc>// H3 with ID</jc>
053 *    H3 <jv>withId</jv> = <jsm>h3</jsm>(<js>"Troubleshooting"</js>)
054 *       .id(<js>"troubleshooting"</js>);
055 * 
056 *    <jc>// H3 with styling</jc>
057 *    H3 <jv>styled2</jv> = <jsm>h3</jsm>(<js>"Common Issues"</js>)
058 *       .style(<js>"color: #888; margin-top: 20px;"</js>);
059 * 
060 *    <jc>// H3 with multiple elements</jc>
061 *    H3 <jv>multiple</jv> = <jsm>h3</jsm>(
062 *       <js>"3.1 "</js>,
063 *       <jsm>span</jsm>()._class(<js>"step-title"</js>).children(<js>"Installation"</js>),
064 *       <js>" "</js>,
065 *       <jsm>small</jsm>(<js>"(5 minutes)"</js>)
066 *    );
067 * 
068 *    <jc>// H3 with links</jc>
069 *    H3 <jv>withLinks</jv> = <jsm>h3</jsm>(
070 *       <js>"See also: "</js>,
071 *       <jsm>a</jsm>(<js>"/docs/faq"</js>).children(<js>"Frequently Asked Questions"</js>)
072 *    );
073 * </p>
074 *
075 * <p>
076 * The following convenience methods are provided for constructing instances of this bean:
077 * <ul class='javatree'>
078 *    <li class='jc'>{@link HtmlBuilder}
079 *    <ul class='javatree'>
080 *       <li class='jm'>{@link HtmlBuilder#h3() h3()}
081 *       <li class='jm'>{@link HtmlBuilder#h3(Object, Object...) h3(Object, Object...)}
082 *    </ul>
083 * </ul>
084 * </p>
085 *
086 * <h5 class='section'>See Also:</h5><ul>
087 *    <li class='link'><a class="doclink" href="https://juneau.apache.org/docs/topics/JuneauBeanHtml5">juneau-bean-html5</a>
088 * </ul>
089 */
090@Bean(typeName="h3")
091@FluentSetters
092public class H3 extends HtmlElementMixed {

094   /**
095    * Creates an empty {@link H3} element.

099   /**
100    * Creates an {@link H3} element with the specified child nodes.
101    *
102    * @param children The child nodes.
103    */
104   public H3(Object...children) {
105      children(children);
106   }
